  "source": "Obstentrics_Williams_textbook_data.txt: Pruritic urticarial papules and plaques of pregnancy (PUPPP), also known as polymorphic eruption of pregnancy, is the most common pruritic dermatological condition in pregnancy, affecting about 1 in 160 pregnancies. The condition typically begins on the abdomen, often within striae distensae, with erythematous, urticarial papules that coalesce into plaques, and then spreads to the thighs, buttocks, and arms. PUPPP predominantly affects primigravidas in the third trimester and usually resolves spontaneously within days of delivery.",
